records.addlTxt: Marquette County DNA Proof of Submission

Defendant Sebastian L. Warren in court.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that an offer was provided and there is resolution today.    Atty Hendee states plea agreement.  Defendant agrees.  Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.  Defendant waives their right to an attorney.    Court finds waiver made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  
Defendant enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  

BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty.

BY THE COURT:  Court orders 5 days in the Marquette County Jail; consecutive to any other sentence
Credit = 4 days
Time Served
Court Costs = $243.00
DNA Sample + $200.00 Surcharge
  Defendant agrees to the $15.00 payment plan fee.
Payment Plan:  $50.00/month commencing on February 1, 2017

Pre-trial conference on December 13, 2016 at 09:45 am.

Defendant Sebastian L. Warren in court, in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Atty Hendee states that bond needs to be set.
 Court confirms the defendant's address.  Defendant received a copy of the criminal complaint & waives it's reading.  Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.  Defendant understands.  Court finds probable cause to support the charges.

  BY THE COURT:  Court enters a Not Guilty plea on behalf of the defendant.

  Atty Hendee states that the defendant is on a PO hold; given that, the State has no objection to a signature bond with conditions.
  BY THE COURT:  Court sets a $500 Signature bond with conditions:


Court questions the defendant.    Defendant waives their right to an attorney in order to have a conference with the District Attorney.    Court finds waiver of Attorney made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.
